# AIUP — Alfresco extension development (Cursor)

You are working in a repository that follows **AIUP** (AI Unified Process) for Alfresco Content Services extensions.

## Mandatory first step

Before generating, editing, or reviewing Alfresco-related code (Java under Alfresco modules, `alfresco/module/**`, content models, web scripts, BPMN workflows, Quartz scheduled jobs, repository patches, transforms, Share/ACA UI extensions, Spring Boot event listeners, `compose.yaml`, etc.), **read and follow** the project rules in **`AGENTS.md`** at the repository root. Treat `AGENTS.md` as the single source of truth for stack versions, layout, naming, forbidden patterns, and testing conventions.

In consumer projects with a submodule at `tools/aiup-alfresco/`, read **`tools/aiup-alfresco/AGENTS.md`** instead (subject to any local version override rule).

## How AIUP commands map here

Cursor 2.4+ exposes AIUP steps as **slash commands** via Agent Skills in `.cursor/skills/`:

- Type **`/requirements`**, **`/scaffold`**, **`/content-model`**, etc. in Agent chat
- Each command skill has `disable-model-invocation: true` — it runs only when explicitly invoked
- Command skills point at `commands/<name>.md` (or `tools/aiup-alfresco/commands/<name>.md` in consumer repos)

Fallbacks when slash commands are not used:

- **`commands/<name>.md`** — full procedure; open via `@commands/<name>.md`
- **`.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`** — validators (auto-triggered) and agent guidance
- **`aiup-alfresco`** orchestrator skill — lists all commands when the step name is unclear
- **`./scripts/aiup-command.sh render --agent cursor <command>`** — portable rendered prompt

When the user asks to run an AIUP step without naming a file, match the request to the closest `/command` or use the **`aiup-alfresco`** orchestrator.

## Output expectations

When an AIUP command requires file output, **create or update real files** in the repo; do not stop at a high-level summary unless the user only asked for a plan.

## Consumer project install

From an Alfresco project root with submodule at `tools/aiup-alfresco/`:

`./tools/aiup-alfresco/scripts/install-cursor-pack.sh`

Re-run after `git submodule update` to refresh slash-command skills.

See **`CURSOR.md`** and **`CURSOR-INTEGRATION-GUIDE.md`** for installation, hooks, and troubleshooting.
